    "Comparison Between Fine-Tuned Zephyr and Fine-Tuned T5 ModelsFigure 5 shows the partial F1 and partial recall results of the fine-tuned T5 and fine-tuned Zephyr models.",
    "The partial F1 score of a fine-tuned T5 is higher compared with Zephyr for all selected entities.",
    "Especially for product combinations, T5 performs much better than Zephyr with the given prompt.",
    "Fig. 5 Partial F1 score and recall results (median and standard deviation) of entities from stratified cross-validation with fine-tuned T5 and fine-tuned Zephyr models.",
    "AE, adverse event; PDC, product dose)."
